Visiting bongo star Mbosso is the newest member of Wasafi Records. You probably remember him from the famous boy band Yamoto Band. It broke the hearts of avid fans when they split. In an interview with Word Is, Mbosso revealed why he left Yamoto Band. "Cha kwanza naeza sema ni maslahi, income ukipenda. Hela mnazopata mnakula na watu wengi sana zilikua hazitoshi, so kila mtu akaamua kufanya mziki kivyake. Hakuna tatizo lolote lingine. Ata sahizi huwa bado tunawasiliana, tunapatana na kupiga stori," he said. Mbosso also talked about life after being signed by WCB. "Challenges ziko. Tulikua tunaimba wanne kabla ya kila mtu kujitenga. Sasa hivi lazima nimalize kwanzia intro mpaka outro. Si rahisi. After hapo niende kufuatilia maswala ya video, kisha nianze kuzunguka kwa media tour ili kujiandaa na show," he said. "Huwa ni changamoto ambayo sasa hivi nko mimi mwenyewe. Sasa labda tufanye collaboration in future, but hatuwezi rudi kuwa pamoja." How did he end up being in Wasafi Record? "Niliingia WCB kwa sababu ya urafiki mzuri, ambapo baadhi ya wasanii wa WCB mi ni favourite wa Diamond tangu zamani. Nakumbuka tangu nikiwa form 2, niliwai fanya naye wimbo, baadae akaja kuniona kwenye YaMoto Band. Na mara kwa mara akiwa kwenye interview zake, lazima anizungumzie: 'Nampenda sana Mbosso na natamani sana kufanya naye kazi'," Mbosso said. "Kwa hivyo mimi kuwa WCB nmekua ni sehemu ya wish ya Diamond. Alitamani siku moja afanye kazi na mimi. "Kufanya kazi na Diamond inanipa fursa na changamoto ya kuweza kufanya ngoma mzuri zaidi ambacho ni kitu kizuri."